This paper is primarily focused on the development of machine learning-based malware detection techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of AI-based anti-malware solutions, which could potentially fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the creation of a framework for collecting and classifying web traffic, which could fall under the categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
